# Vendored verbatim from
# https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye/blob/master/reasoning/backward-more/backward-more.n3
# (no truncation needed -- the upstream file is already small). This is a
# distinct backward-chaining case from the existing `vendored/backward_math.n3`
# (which proves a single ground goal via a lone `math:greaterThan`-guarded
# rule with no ground facts to recurse over): this file has THREE distinct
# `<=` rules over a small ground fact base --
#   R1: score-comparison (`math:greaterThan` over `:score` facts)
#   R2: independent award/boring context rule (no shared predicate with R1)
#   R3: genuine *recursive* backward transitivity (`?X :moreInterestingThan
#       ?Y. ?Y :moreInterestingThan ?Z.` chaining through R1/R2's derived
#       facts as well as the ground `:B :moreInterestingThan :C` fact) --
# giving real multi-rule interaction and backward-chained recursion depth
# not exercised by any of the 15 previously-vendored cases.
#
# This engine's `TripleStore::prove` (the `prove_goal` manifest mechanism
# used by `backward_math`/`peano`) was checked against this file during
# vendoring and found to return `true` unconditionally for every goal tried
# -- including goals against completely unrelated facts and even against an
# empty store with no rules at all. That is a real, reproducible bug in
# `TripleStore::prove` independent of this file, out of scope for this
# vendoring batch to fix; it means `prove_goal` cannot honestly be used as
# evidence right now for *any* case (existing or new). This case is
# therefore vendored using the ordinary forward `materialize()` + `expected`
# subset-check mechanism instead, which was independently confirmed (by
# actually running `TripleStore::materialize()` on this exact input) to
# correctly derive the real EYE-answer facts for backward-more-query1/2/3
# (`:A :moreInterestingThan :B`, `:D :moreInterestingThan :B`, and the R3
# transitive derivations `:A/:D :moreInterestingThan :C`) and nothing
# spurious.
@prefix math: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/math#>.
@prefix log: <http://www.w3.org/2000/10/swap/log#>.
@prefix : <http://example.org/#>.

# table moreInterestingThan
[] log:table :moreInterestingThan.

# Scores (ground facts)
:A :score 8.
:B :score 5.

# Base edge to enable A > C by transitivity (no score for C):
:B :moreInterestingThan :C.

# Contextual facts for the award/boring rule: D > B
:D :hasAward true.
:B :boring true.

# R1: by score
{
    ?X :moreInterestingThan ?Y.
} <= {
    ?X :score ?SX.
    ?Y :score ?SY.
    ?SX math:greaterThan ?SY.
}.

# R2: award/boring context
{
    ?X :moreInterestingThan ?Y.
} <= {
    ?X :hasAward true.
    ?Y :boring true.
}.

# R3: transitivity (recursive)
{
    ?X :moreInterestingThan ?Z.
} <= {
    ?X :moreInterestingThan ?Y.
    ?Y :moreInterestingThan ?Z.
}.
